"And this is why it is not known with what mechanism and at what price the problematic assets will be bought.
This will be decisive for the sharing of losses between the financial sector and the government," Marek said this week, for the iHNed.cz server.
Whether the plan is approved now or early next week is not, according to Marek, all that relevant.
"Much more important is that, already this week the congressmen agree on their support and give their approval as soon as possible.
This important and psychological agreement to reach that approval is, at this time, the most important thing," Marek insisted.
Triumph of the populist right in Austria, together they form 29%
The early elections to the Austrian parliament have brought, according to the first approximate results, an appreciable weakening of both parties of the current grand coalition and an expressive strengthening of the party of the populist right.
Heavy and special losses have suffered the Austrian People's Party (OVP), where the position of the current president, Wilhelm Molterer, is seriously faltering.
On the contrary, the leader of the Alliance for the Future of Austria (BZO), the head of the government of the state of Carinthia, Jörg Haider, prepares his triumphant return to national politics.
According to the rough results, the Social Democracy (SPÖ) remains the strongest party in the country with 29.8 percent of the vote, losing 5.5 percent of the vote compared to the last elections in 2006.
Even worse is the OVP losing 25.6 percent, almost nine percent of votes.
They are the worst results, literally catastrophic, in the history of these two great Austrian parties since the post-war period and especially for the popular ones who called these early elections.
Even at the beginning of July, when the OVP left the coalition, the popular had a considerable advantage in terms of preference over the SPO.
It is clear, however, that voters punished them for letting the government sink.
Already in the first reactions to the results, speculation was heard about the resignation of the party president and, until today, vice-chancellor, Wilhelm Molterer.
Observers believe that as early as Monday it could be reached at the exceptional meeting of the party presidency.
Such a development would obviously pave the way for the constant and closer starting point of the electoral results, that is, the renewal of the grand coalition between SPO and OVP.
In view of the fact that the reinforcement of both parties of the populist right - the liberals (FPO) have won approximately 18 percent and the BZO, eleven percent of the vote - and that the social democrats at the same time expressed their fears that the same thing of 1999 would be repeated when the popular negotiated with the populists (then FPO was a unit,  but in 2005 it was dismembered from BZO) for a coalition government that came to generate a sanction by the European Union.
Haider is clearly committed to this evolution, who has already announced that he is prepared to collaborate with any party and that he is already assuming his return to Vienna, to national politics.
The Green Party has also managed to reach the parliament although it has lost slightly and fell from third to fifth place among Austrian political parties.
No other party clearly exceeded the four percent limit and therefore is not part of parliament.
Armed fighting: MP3 Player against mobile.
We advise you how to choose
While almost all mobile plays MP3 files, no MP3 player manages to make calls.
What seems clear is that it is better to buy only the phone.
Even so, there are enough reasons for man to acquire only the breeder.
The choice depends practically on the manner of its use and the requirement of the future owner.
It will probably be difficult for him to acquire the most modern turntable to listen to Maxim Turbulenc's latest album.
On the other hand, this type of musical products such as LP discs no longer come out, and as far as their quality is concerned, there is not a single objective reason to continue buying them.
If vinyl records with art rock, jazz or blues music crowd your shelves, you are probably dreaming, at least, of this type of turntable.
This is the same with music that is on the way, i.e. compressed, simplified music - MP3 music.
And here there are categories of price and quality.
For some it may be unacceptable to spend eight thousand crowns on a player, the same as for a Pink Floyd lover who will hardly try the market helmets of twenty crowns.
