The MHD of Prague takes us on Wednesday for the first time with the chip
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008, the history of the Prague Transport Company is written the date on which the first passengers enter the metro, tram and bus with an electronic voucher in their pockets instead of a paper ticket.
This can be purchased right now by almost one hundred thousand people who own the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy the 30-day, 90-day and annual passes (this will be valid from January 1, 2009) and simultaneously load it on their chip card at the infocenters and kiosks of the transport company in the Metro stations, Muzeum, Můstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy,  Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
The vouchers can be purchased since yesterday on the internet on the pages of the transport company, www.dpp.cz.
