In connection with the tragic accident of the bus of the company Student Agency near the Italian city of Padova we have the question of whether stewardesses and passengers can move around the bus during the trip.
"If we wanted to strictly and formally comply with the law, the activity of the stewardess is contrary to the road traffic law," says transport ministry spokesman Karel Hanzelka.
The accident in which the twenty-two-year-old flight attendant died last week was evidently caused by the truck driver only that the bus crossed the road.
The girl, unfortunately, was sitting next to the driver in the least safe place of the vehicle despite having reserved two other places.
However, the bus can have an accident or brake suddenly, and at the precise moment when the steward distributes coffee or newspapers.
Here what plays the role is whether the bus is equipped, according to the technical permit, with places on foot.
If the bus is not approved, the passenger must be seated.
Student Agency's long-distance buses have no standing seats, company director Radim Jančura confirmed to Aktuálně.cz.
"We have solved this with the ministry and, in principle, the movement of passengers is not allowed.
