The road transport law only knows the term Vehicle Inspector, whose rights and obligations are not defined," adds spokesman Hanzelka less bluntly.
Josef Pokorný, director of the Department of Road Traffic at the Ministry of Transport, believes that the law sufficiently addresses this problem.
"It depends on whether the bus has the approval allowed to have places on foot.
That's it," he says.
The buses are divided between the urban ones, where there are places to stand and of limited maximum speed, intercity with places to stand with a greater speed permit and those of long distances without places to stand, with the highest speed permit and with seats equipped with seat belts.
Like on the plane, says the expert
BESIP's expert in transport safety, Jaroslav Hořín, does not see major problems regarding the movement of the steward on the bus.
"During the development of the trip there is not much threat of danger, the situation can be compared to the service on the planes.
