A huge tragedy happened
In the accident on the line to Naples, a young stewardess from Pilsen who had worked for the company for two years died.
A Slovenian truck that probably veered from the parking lane blocking the way to the bus. without using the turn signals.
His driver tried in a quick maneuver to avoid him, however, he collided with the front right side.
Jančura denies that the two sites that are reserved for the hostess's rest were sold.
"These sites cannot be reserved for long-distance connections, they are blocked."
The company intends to sue the truck driver.
The agency will not wait for the verdict of the trial on the compensation of the girl's family but expects the financial expenses also from the guilty party.
Law reform?
No, for now
The reform of the law could bring greater precision about the movement of the stewardess on the bus in which thirty experts members of a group of the Ministry of Transport have been working for a year.
"However, they have not come to any concrete conclusions.
They are not too much dedicated to buses, but rather to the point system, maximum speed on the motorway and the use of the mobile phone while driving," says expert Hořín.
"The Ministry of Transport does not consider the activity of stewardesses something that significantly threatens the safety of passengers," spokesman Hanzelka concluded, that the control of security on buses is the responsibility of the police and the Office of Safety at Work.
